Kultura tops and ternos and other Kultura Products

Hello!

Most of the Kultura products are beautiful and craftsmanship finely executed and done.When I go home for vacation to Cebu Philippines I never miss and I always have to check and buy a beautifully handcrafted products whether a fine pearl of the orient brooch or a panuelo or Maria Clara inspired sleeves bolero ..
There are millions of Filipinos and other ethnic individuals living and working abroad who are not able to go home to the Philippines to obtain Filipino wear but would rather order online. They want to lay their hands on Kultura ! Filipino wear are so in demand specially when Filipinos living abroad are celebrating Filipino events like Independence Day every June month and cultural programs wanting to showcase what they are wearing..vying as to who has the beautiful Filipino wear! “ Parang nag fashion show”! Filipinos wear harongs ,tops and gowns on special occasions such as during weddings , entertaining dignitaries, state dinners specially when hosting events . I can always tell which ones are from Kultura.The only drawback ,I find ,is that prices are steep for those who are counting their every bit of earnings and not every OFW’s be able to purchase your products as much as they want to order and have. There are other competitions companies offering much lesser price selling Filipino inspired barongs and women’s tops and dresses but I rather have and own a wear from Kultura… Kultura captures my mood and taste! It boost my confidence when I’m wearing Kultura Filipiniana!
I must confess I love to own Kultura wear but I think I’ll wait till your products go on sale if ever you do have sales! I don’t want to sound cheap but just being realistic specially in these challenging times and economy…I keep on dreaming!🥰

Mabuhay Philippines! Mabuhay Kultura!

Hazel
